	"thecritterpack:handbooktext-nestpoint": "Place nest down in a spot your female ducks have access to. The ducks will lay eggs in a nest by preference, not on the ground. Once the nest has 5 eggs, a broody duck will sit incubating those eggs until they hatch.<br><br>For viable eggs, ducks must have access to a male duck! ducks must be <a href=\"handbook://block-trough-genericwood-small-ns\">well fed</a> to lay! A broody duck needs to have a full belly before it will sit for a day!<br><br>If every nest is occupied, ducks may lay eggs on the ground, which can then be picked up. The player can also collect eggs from a nest, by <hk>rightmouse</hk>-clicking.",
	
	
